<font color="#FF0000">SOME CLARIFICATION</font><br>
<tt>Sat Apr 26  1:53:16 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
A small note and an observation - It was noted that there might be some confusion when I or others refer to my daughter. I was ask to clear confusion. What Chet had refered to was my adopted daughter of Asian descent was unfortunate enough to have opened e-mail meant for me but contained hate language with references to her. Obviously, this caused her hurt. <br><br>
I have another daughter who died and was buried at Punchbowl National Cemetary of the Pacific.<br><br>
And probably the reason why the issue with the cemetaries is not big news &quot;over there&quot; is because we are &quot;over here&quot;.  Hawaii is hardly big news, even when a town is leveled by a lava flow via volcano.<br><br>
Second reason is that hate crimes are too common on the mainland and have lost their news value. Its been a long time since I heard anything about church fires. In Hawaii, this is big news as it is not common here. In the past couple years or so, militia groups have spilled over from the mainland to over here. This hate group might be a new chapter of an old mainland group. Who knows?<br><br>
And, no, we don't need vigilantism. Our cops are good and the FBI is heavily invested, after all, federal grounds were involved. I'm not the gipper. Too late and one too much bourbon and branchwater, Doc. And, in the scheme of things, it is a small matter.  Enough said.
